{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EW9TAVMApisb7g7B1neB6C","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary: Cloche Codebase Exploration\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase. Here are my key findings:\n\n### 1. **CLI SUBCOMMAND PATTERN** (`cmd/cloche/`)\n\nThe CLI is structured as a command dispatcher in `main.go`:\n\n**File: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`**\n- Single `main()` function that parses `os.Args[1]` to determine the command\n- Commands split into two categories:\n  - **No daemon needed**: `init`, `health`\n  - **Require gRPC connection**: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `list`, `stop`, `delete`, `orchestrate`, `shutdown`\n\n**Pattern for adding new commands:**\n1. Add case in the switch statement (lines 30-78)\n2. Create a `cmd<CommandName>(...)` function in a separate file\n3. For gRPC commands: function signature is `func cmd<Name>(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string)`\n4. For non-gRPC commands: function signature is `func cmd<Name>(args []string)`\n\n**Existing command implementations:**\n- `cmdInit()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` - scaffolds new projects\n- `cmdHealth()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/health.go` - queries HTTP health endpoint\n- `cmdRun()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 102-162) - launches workflow\n- `cmdStatus()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 164-201) - checks run status\n- `cmdLogs()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 249-330) - streams run logs\n- `cmdPoll()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go` - waits for run completion\n- `cmdList()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 203-247) - lists runs\n- `cmdStop()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 394-406) - stops running workflow\n- `cmdDelete()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 408-420) - deletes containers\n- `cmdOrchestrate()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 422-434) - **deprecated/removed** (returns error at server side)\n- `cmdShutdown()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 436-443) - graceful daemon shutdown\n\n### 2. **GRPC SERVICE DEFINITION**\n\n**File: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`**\n\nThe proto file currently defines (7 RPCs):\n```protobuf\nservice ClocheService {\n  rpc RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) returns (RunWorkflowResponse);\n  rpc GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) returns (GetStatusResponse);\n  rpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) returns (stream LogEntry);\n  rpc StopRun(StopRunRequest) returns (StopRunResponse);\n  rpc ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse);\n  rpc Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) returns (ShutdownResponse);\n  rpc DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) returns (DeleteContainerResponse);\n}\n```\n\n**Generated code:** `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go` and `cloche_grpc.pb.go`\n- **IMPORTANT**: The generated pb.go files contain `OrchestrateRequest` and `OrchestrateResponse` message types with the `Orchestrate` RPC, but the **source proto file does NOT** have these definitions yet. This means the proto has been modified in the generated files only (likely during development).\n\n**Key message types:**\n- `RunWorkflowRequest` - includes: workflow_name, project_dir, image, prompt, keep_container, title\n- `RunWorkflowResponse` - returns: run_id\n- `GetStatusRequest/Response` - run status with step executions, container info, error tracking\n- `StreamLogsRequest` - filters by step_name, log_type\n- `ListRunsRequest/Response` - with optional `all` flag to show all or just last hour\n- `OrchestrateRequest` - includes: project_dir\n- `OrchestrateResponse` - includes: dispatched (int32, count of dispatched runs)\n\n### 3. **DAEMON & GRPC SERVER** (`cmd/cloched/`, `internal/adapters/grpc/`)\n\n**File: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`**\n\nDaemon startup:\n1. Loads global config from `~/.config/cloche/config`\n2. Creates SQLite store (`cloche.db`)\n3. Sweeps stale runs from previous crashes\n4. Initializes container runtime (docker or local)\n5. Creates gRPC server with `ClocheServer` implementation\n6. Auto-runs active projects via `autoRunActiveProjects()` which launches host workflows\n7. Optionally starts HTTP server for web dashboard\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`**\n\n`ClocheServer` struct implements `ClocheServiceServer`:\n- **Fields**: store, captures, logStore, container runtime, defaultImage, evolution trigger, logBroadcaster\n- **Key methods**:\n  - `RunWorkflow()` - creates run, launches container in background goroutine\n  - `launchAndTrack()` - starts container and tracks it to completion (background goroutine)\n  - `trackRun()` - reads status messages from container, updates run state, extracts results to git branch, indexes logs\n  - `GetStatus()` - returns run status with step executions\n  - `StreamLogs()` - server-streaming RPC for log entries\n  - `ListRuns()` - lists runs (all or last hour)\n  - `StopRun()` - stops running container\n  - `DeleteContainer()` - removes retained containers\n  - **`Orchestrate()`** - at line 669-671, **returns error** \"orchestrator has been removed; use host workflow instead\"\n  - `Shutdown()` - graceful daemon shutdown\n  - `SetLogStore()`, `SetEvolution()`, `SetLogBroadcaster()`, `SetShutdownFunc()` - dependency setters\n\n### 4. **HOST WORKFLOW EXECUTOR** (`internal/host/`)\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`**\n\n`Executor` struct implements `engine.StepExecutor` for host workflow steps:\n- **Executes two step types**:\n  - `StepTypeScript` - shell commands via `exec.CommandContext()`\n  - `StepTypeWorkflow` - dispatches container workflow runs via gRPC `RunWorkflow()` and waits for completion\n- **Environment variables** passed to steps:\n  - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - project directory\n  - `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - where to write step output\n  - `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - previous step's output (if available)\n  - Plus any output mappings from wiring\n- **Output mapping** - resolves wires to extract values from previous step outputs (supports JSON path navigation)\n- **Key methods**:\n  - `Execute()` - dispatches to executeScript or executeWorkflow\n  - `executeScript()` - runs shell command, captures output, marks with result (success/fail)\n  - `executeWorkflow()` - dispatches container workflow, reads prompt from previous step output, polls until run completes\n  - `waitForRun()` - polls store every 2 seconds until run reaches terminal state\n  - `resolveOutputMappings()` - evaluates JSON paths for output mappings from wires\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`**\n\n`Runner` struct orchestrates host workflow execution:\n- **Fields**: Dispatcher (RunDispatcher interface for gRPC calls), Store (RunStore)\n- **Key methods**:\n  - `Run()` - main entry point:\n    1. Reads `.cloche/host.cloche`\n    2. Parses it (must be workflow named \"main\")\n    3. Generates unique orchestration run ID\n    4. Creates run record in store (marked with `IsHost = true`)\n    5. Creates `Executor` with step output directory\n    6. Creates `Engine` and sets status handler\n    7. Walks the workflow graph via `Engine.Run()`\n    8. Updates run state with final result\n  - Status handler methods log and persist step start/complete events to store\n\n**Integration point with daemon:** \n- In `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` at lines 196-232, `autoRunActiveProjects()` function:\n  - Scans active projects (marked with `active = true` in config)\n  - Launches a `Runner.Run()` goroutine for each active project's host workflow\n  - Host workflows can dispatch container workflows via the server's `RunWorkflow()` method\n\n### 5. **EXECUTION MODEL & WORKFLOW ENGINE** (`internal/engine/`, `internal/domain/`)\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`**\n\n- **StepType enum**: `agent`, `script`, `workflow`\n- **WorkflowLocation enum**: `container` (for .cloche/*.cloche files), `host` (for .cloche/host.cloche)\n- **Workflow struct**: Name, Location, Steps (map), Wiring ([]Wire), Collects, EntryStep, Config\n- **Wire struct**: From, Result, To (with OutputMap for data passing)\n- **Step struct**: Name, Type, Results (possible outcomes), Config (key-value pairs)\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`**\n\n`Engine` struct walks the workflow DAG:\n- Implements step dispatch, result validation, wiring resolution, collect clause handling\n- Uses goroutines to execute steps concurrently when DAG allows\n- Main event loop receives step completions and dispatches next steps based on wiring\n- Calls `StepExecutor.Execute()` interface for each step (implemented differently for containers vs host)\n\n**Run struct** (`internal/domain/run.go`):\n- Tracks: ID, WorkflowName, State (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled)\n- Records step executions with timing\n- For host runs: `IsHost = true`\n- For container runs: tracks ContainerID, BaseSHA (for git branch creation)\n\n### 6. **KEY ORCHESTRATION FACTS**\n\n1. **Old \"orchestrator\" has been removed** - see line 670 in server.go and the error message. It was hardcoded Go logic for pulling tasks, generating prompts, dispatching container runs.\n\n2. **Host workflows are the new orchestration mechanism** - instead of hardcoded logic, projects define `.cloche/host.cloche` with custom orchestration steps.\n\n3. **Host workflow dispatch flow**:\n   - Daemon startup detects active projects\n   - Spawns `Runner.Run()` goroutine for each\n   - Runner parses and executes host.cloche workflow step-by-step\n   - Host steps can dispatch container workflows and wait for them\n   - Results are extracted to git branches\n\n4. **Existing \"orchestrate\" RPC is stubbed out** - the CLI command `cloche orchestrate` still exists and calls the RPC, but the server returns an error telling users to use host workflows instead.\n\n### 7. **PROJECT STRUCTURE**\n\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/           ← CLI client (command dispatcher)\n    main.go         ← Command switch, most cmd functions\n    init.go         ← Project initialization\n    health.go       ← Health check via HTTP\n    poll.go         ← Wait for run completion\n    orchestrate_test.go ← Test for command output format\n\ncmd/cloched/        ← Daemon process\n  main.go           ← Server setup, gRPC listener, auto-run active projects\n\ncmd/cloche-agent/   ← In-container execution (separate binary)\n\ninternal/\n  domain/           ← Core types\n    workflow.go     ← Workflow, Step, Wire definitions\n    run.go          ← Run and RunState\n\n  engine/           ← Generic workflow execution\n    engine.go       ← Workflow DAG walker\n\n  host/             ← Host workflow execution\n    runner.go       ← Host workflow orchestrator (reads host.cloche)\n    executor.go     ← Step execution (scripts vs container workflows)\n\n  adapters/\n    grpc/\n      server.go     ← gRPC service implementation (ClocheServer)\n    docker/         ← Container runtime\n    sqlite/         ← Persistence\n    web/            ← HTTP dashboard\n\n  ports/            ← Interfaces\n    store.go        ← RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore, EvolutionStore\n    container.go    ← ContainerRuntime interface\n\napi/\n  proto/cloche/v1/\n    cloche.proto    ← Service definition (source)\n  clochepb/         ← Generated code\n    cloche.pb.go\n    cloche_grpc.pb.go\n```\n\n### 8. **ADDING NEW FEATURES**\n\n**Pattern for new CLI subcommand:**\n1. Add case in `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` main switch (around line 56-78)\n2. Create `cmdNewCommand()` function in separate file or in main.go\n3. Call client method from gRPC service\n4. Add to usage() help text\n\n**Pattern for new gRPC RPC:**\n1. Add to proto service definition in `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n2. Add message types (Request/Response)\n3. Run `protoc` to regenerate pb.go files (see Makefile)\n4. Implement handler in `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n5. Create corresponding CLI command\n\n**Pattern for new daemon logic:**\n- Implement via host workflow steps (preferred)\n- Or extend gRPC service with new RPC\n- Or hook into status events via StatusHandler interface\n\n---\n\n### Key Files Summary (Absolute Paths):\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI entry point and most commands\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` - Project initialization command\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` - Daemon startup\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - gRPC service definition (SOURCE)\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go` - Generated protobuf code\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go` - Generated gRPC code\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC service implementation\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - Host workflow orchestrator\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - Host step executor\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` - Workflow DAG walker\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Core workflow types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run state tracking\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - Storage interfaces\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` - Container runtime interface"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a400081154a1695b7 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68855\ntool_uses: 46\nduration_ms: 95198</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e86d396b-c477-4111-8724-c79fdb5bf532","uuid":"bc3eed72-44cc-46f6-8d2c-aa5c0d890306","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand:\n1. How existing CLI subcommands are structured (look at cmd/cloche/ directory)\n2. The gRPC service definition (proto files)\n3. How the orchestrator works (host workflow executor)\n4. How existing commands like `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop` are implemented\n5. The daemon's gRPC server implementation\n\nBe very thorough - read the key files fully. I need to understand:\n- The pattern for adding new CLI subcommands\n- The gRPC proto definitions\n- The daemon server handler\n- The orchestrator/host workflow executor\n- Any existing \"orchestrate\" references\n\nSearch for files matching: cmd/cloche/*.go, cmd/cloched/*.go, internal/host/*.go, *.proto, internal/adapters/grpc/*.go","agentId":"a400081154a1695b7","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary: Cloche Codebase Exploration\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase. Here are my key findings:\n\n### 1. **CLI SUBCOMMAND PATTERN** (`cmd/cloche/`)\n\nThe CLI is structured as a command dispatcher in `main.go`:\n\n**File: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`**\n- Single `main()` function that parses `os.Args[1]` to determine the command\n- Commands split into two categories:\n  - **No daemon needed**: `init`, `health`\n  - **Require gRPC connection**: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `list`, `stop`, `delete`, `orchestrate`, `shutdown`\n\n**Pattern for adding new commands:**\n1. Add case in the switch statement (lines 30-78)\n2. Create a `cmd<CommandName>(...)` function in a separate file\n3. For gRPC commands: function signature is `func cmd<Name>(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string)`\n4. For non-gRPC commands: function signature is `func cmd<Name>(args []string)`\n\n**Existing command implementations:**\n- `cmdInit()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` - scaffolds new projects\n- `cmdHealth()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/health.go` - queries HTTP health endpoint\n- `cmdRun()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 102-162) - launches workflow\n- `cmdStatus()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 164-201) - checks run status\n- `cmdLogs()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 249-330) - streams run logs\n- `cmdPoll()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go` - waits for run completion\n- `cmdList()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 203-247) - lists runs\n- `cmdStop()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 394-406) - stops running workflow\n- `cmdDelete()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 408-420) - deletes containers\n- `cmdOrchestrate()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 422-434) - **deprecated/removed** (returns error at server side)\n- `cmdShutdown()` - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 436-443) - graceful daemon shutdown\n\n### 2. **GRPC SERVICE DEFINITION**\n\n**File: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`**\n\nThe proto file currently defines (7 RPCs):\n```protobuf\nservice ClocheService {\n  rpc RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) returns (RunWorkflowResponse);\n  rpc GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) returns (GetStatusResponse);\n  rpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) returns (stream LogEntry);\n  rpc StopRun(StopRunRequest) returns (StopRunResponse);\n  rpc ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse);\n  rpc Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) returns (ShutdownResponse);\n  rpc DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) returns (DeleteContainerResponse);\n}\n```\n\n**Generated code:** `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go` and `cloche_grpc.pb.go`\n- **IMPORTANT**: The generated pb.go files contain `OrchestrateRequest` and `OrchestrateResponse` message types with the `Orchestrate` RPC, but the **source proto file does NOT** have these definitions yet. This means the proto has been modified in the generated files only (likely during development).\n\n**Key message types:**\n- `RunWorkflowRequest` - includes: workflow_name, project_dir, image, prompt, keep_container, title\n- `RunWorkflowResponse` - returns: run_id\n- `GetStatusRequest/Response` - run status with step executions, container info, error tracking\n- `StreamLogsRequest` - filters by step_name, log_type\n- `ListRunsRequest/Response` - with optional `all` flag to show all or just last hour\n- `OrchestrateRequest` - includes: project_dir\n- `OrchestrateResponse` - includes: dispatched (int32, count of dispatched runs)\n\n### 3. **DAEMON & GRPC SERVER** (`cmd/cloched/`, `internal/adapters/grpc/`)\n\n**File: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`**\n\nDaemon startup:\n1. Loads global config from `~/.config/cloche/config`\n2. Creates SQLite store (`cloche.db`)\n3. Sweeps stale runs from previous crashes\n4. Initializes container runtime (docker or local)\n5. Creates gRPC server with `ClocheServer` implementation\n6. Auto-runs active projects via `autoRunActiveProjects()` which launches host workflows\n7. Optionally starts HTTP server for web dashboard\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`**\n\n`ClocheServer` struct implements `ClocheServiceServer`:\n- **Fields**: store, captures, logStore, container runtime, defaultImage, evolution trigger, logBroadcaster\n- **Key methods**:\n  - `RunWorkflow()` - creates run, launches container in background goroutine\n  - `launchAndTrack()` - starts container and tracks it to completion (background goroutine)\n  - `trackRun()` - reads status messages from container, updates run state, extracts results to git branch, indexes logs\n  - `GetStatus()` - returns run status with step executions\n  - `StreamLogs()` - server-streaming RPC for log entries\n  - `ListRuns()` - lists runs (all or last hour)\n  - `StopRun()` - stops running container\n  - `DeleteContainer()` - removes retained containers\n  - **`Orchestrate()`** - at line 669-671, **returns error** \"orchestrator has been removed; use host workflow instead\"\n  - `Shutdown()` - graceful daemon shutdown\n  - `SetLogStore()`, `SetEvolution()`, `SetLogBroadcaster()`, `SetShutdownFunc()` - dependency setters\n\n### 4. **HOST WORKFLOW EXECUTOR** (`internal/host/`)\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`**\n\n`Executor` struct implements `engine.StepExecutor` for host workflow steps:\n- **Executes two step types**:\n  - `StepTypeScript` - shell commands via `exec.CommandContext()`\n  - `StepTypeWorkflow` - dispatches container workflow runs via gRPC `RunWorkflow()` and waits for completion\n- **Environment variables** passed to steps:\n  - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - project directory\n  - `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - where to write step output\n  - `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - previous step's output (if available)\n  - Plus any output mappings from wiring\n- **Output mapping** - resolves wires to extract values from previous step outputs (supports JSON path navigation)\n- **Key methods**:\n  - `Execute()` - dispatches to executeScript or executeWorkflow\n  - `executeScript()` - runs shell command, captures output, marks with result (success/fail)\n  - `executeWorkflow()` - dispatches container workflow, reads prompt from previous step output, polls until run completes\n  - `waitForRun()` - polls store every 2 seconds until run reaches terminal state\n  - `resolveOutputMappings()` - evaluates JSON paths for output mappings from wires\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`**\n\n`Runner` struct orchestrates host workflow execution:\n- **Fields**: Dispatcher (RunDispatcher interface for gRPC calls), Store (RunStore)\n- **Key methods**:\n  - `Run()` - main entry point:\n    1. Reads `.cloche/host.cloche`\n    2. Parses it (must be workflow named \"main\")\n    3. Generates unique orchestration run ID\n    4. Creates run record in store (marked with `IsHost = true`)\n    5. Creates `Executor` with step output directory\n    6. Creates `Engine` and sets status handler\n    7. Walks the workflow graph via `Engine.Run()`\n    8. Updates run state with final result\n  - Status handler methods log and persist step start/complete events to store\n\n**Integration point with daemon:** \n- In `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` at lines 196-232, `autoRunActiveProjects()` function:\n  - Scans active projects (marked with `active = true` in config)\n  - Launches a `Runner.Run()` goroutine for each active project's host workflow\n  - Host workflows can dispatch container workflows via the server's `RunWorkflow()` method\n\n### 5. **EXECUTION MODEL & WORKFLOW ENGINE** (`internal/engine/`, `internal/domain/`)\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`**\n\n- **StepType enum**: `agent`, `script`, `workflow`\n- **WorkflowLocation enum**: `container` (for .cloche/*.cloche files), `host` (for .cloche/host.cloche)\n- **Workflow struct**: Name, Location, Steps (map), Wiring ([]Wire), Collects, EntryStep, Config\n- **Wire struct**: From, Result, To (with OutputMap for data passing)\n- **Step struct**: Name, Type, Results (possible outcomes), Config (key-value pairs)\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`**\n\n`Engine` struct walks the workflow DAG:\n- Implements step dispatch, result validation, wiring resolution, collect clause handling\n- Uses goroutines to execute steps concurrently when DAG allows\n- Main event loop receives step completions and dispatches next steps based on wiring\n- Calls `StepExecutor.Execute()` interface for each step (implemented differently for containers vs host)\n\n**Run struct** (`internal/domain/run.go`):\n- Tracks: ID, WorkflowName, State (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled)\n- Records step executions with timing\n- For host runs: `IsHost = true`\n- For container runs: tracks ContainerID, BaseSHA (for git branch creation)\n\n### 6. **KEY ORCHESTRATION FACTS**\n\n1. **Old \"orchestrator\" has been removed** - see line 670 in server.go and the error message. It was hardcoded Go logic for pulling tasks, generating prompts, dispatching container runs.\n\n2. **Host workflows are the new orchestration mechanism** - instead of hardcoded logic, projects define `.cloche/host.cloche` with custom orchestration steps.\n\n3. **Host workflow dispatch flow**:\n   - Daemon startup detects active projects\n   - Spawns `Runner.Run()` goroutine for each\n   - Runner parses and executes host.cloche workflow step-by-step\n   - Host steps can dispatch container workflows and wait for them\n   - Results are extracted to git branches\n\n4. **Existing \"orchestrate\" RPC is stubbed out** - the CLI command `cloche orchestrate` still exists and calls the RPC, but the server returns an error telling users to use host workflows instead.\n\n### 7. **PROJECT STRUCTURE**\n\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/           ← CLI client (command dispatcher)\n    main.go         ← Command switch, most cmd functions\n    init.go         ← Project initialization\n    health.go       ← Health check via HTTP\n    poll.go         ← Wait for run completion\n    orchestrate_test.go ← Test for command output format\n\ncmd/cloched/        ← Daemon process\n  main.go           ← Server setup, gRPC listener, auto-run active projects\n\ncmd/cloche-agent/   ← In-container execution (separate binary)\n\ninternal/\n  domain/           ← Core types\n    workflow.go     ← Workflow, Step, Wire definitions\n    run.go          ← Run and RunState\n\n  engine/           ← Generic workflow execution\n    engine.go       ← Workflow DAG walker\n\n  host/             ← Host workflow execution\n    runner.go       ← Host workflow orchestrator (reads host.cloche)\n    executor.go     ← Step execution (scripts vs container workflows)\n\n  adapters/\n    grpc/\n      server.go     ← gRPC service implementation (ClocheServer)\n    docker/         ← Container runtime\n    sqlite/         ← Persistence\n    web/            ← HTTP dashboard\n\n  ports/            ← Interfaces\n    store.go        ← RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore, EvolutionStore\n    container.go    ← ContainerRuntime interface\n\napi/\n  proto/cloche/v1/\n    cloche.proto    ← Service definition (source)\n  clochepb/         ← Generated code\n    cloche.pb.go\n    cloche_grpc.pb.go\n```\n\n### 8. **ADDING NEW FEATURES**\n\n**Pattern for new CLI subcommand:**\n1. Add case in `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` main switch (around line 56-78)\n2. Create `cmdNewCommand()` function in separate file or in main.go\n3. Call client method from gRPC service\n4. Add to usage() help text\n\n**Pattern for new gRPC RPC:**\n1. Add to proto service definition in `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n2. Add message types (Request/Response)\n3. Run `protoc` to regenerate pb.go files (see Makefile)\n4. Implement handler in `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n5. Create corresponding CLI command\n\n**Pattern for new daemon logic:**\n- Implement via host workflow steps (preferred)\n- Or extend gRPC service with new RPC\n- Or hook into status events via StatusHandler interface\n\n---\n\n### Key Files Summary (Absolute Paths):\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI entry point and most commands\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` - Project initialization command\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` - Daemon startup\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - gRPC service definition (SOURCE)\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go` - Generated protobuf code\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go` - Generated gRPC code\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC service implementation\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - Host workflow orchestrator\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - Host step executor\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` - Workflow DAG walker\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Core workflow types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run state tracking\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - Storage interfaces\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` - Container runtime interface"}],"totalDurationMs":95198,"totalTokens":68855,"totalToolUseCount":46,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":441,"cache_read_input_tokens":64688,"output_tokens":3721,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":441},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
